<BR>&gt; nice, juicy exp. Imagine how a small group of level 5's (with
<BR>&gt; healing abilities within the group) would be able to hold the
<BR>&gt; bottleneck from Qeynos Hills to Blackburrow while their buddies
<BR>&gt; are mining the top level(BB). After a set period of time, they
<BR>&gt; switch until both halves of the group are ready to move on to
<BR>&gt; the next higher level bottleneck....
<P>&gt; *shudder*
<BR>&gt; *grin*
<P>Yes this is one of problems on PVP run server...problem with large group dominating..imagine 2-3 groups each having 6 members in them just killing anyone in local zone(s)...
<BR>whos there to stop them knowing that severe experience punihment exists upon death...after 1 week many people who have died were set back, and thoe players killing em advanced (by killing spawned monsters)...this is one of unbalanced thigns that will indeed exist..these more organized players will benefit :(
<P>&gt; People best make friends FAST or suffer the consequences....
<P>&gt; Look forward to working with you Geiger. PvP has become MY top
<BR>&gt; priority...(after general pre-customer support, of course :)
<P>&gt; Zariin
